benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01 demonstrates removal of all custom fields with 204 and empty body.
Specific field removal: TC02 demonstrates removal of a subset of fields via the customField query parameter.
Single-field and no-field cases: TC03 and TC04 cover deletion when there is exactly one custom field and when there are no custom fields.
Header variations: TC05 covers all optional headers and TC06 covers only the required header for deletion.
Input validation and error handling: TC07 validates invalid UUID format; TC10 validates malformed customField IDs; TC15 tests injection attempts.
Existence and authorization checks: TC08 tests 404 for non-existent item; TC09 tests missing required header; TC19 tests expired/invalid token.

Parameter resilience: TC11 allows extra query parameters; TC12 handles a large number of IDs; TC17 covers mixed valid/invalid IDs; TC18 covers duplicates in IDs; TC20 validates header formatting regression.
System resiliency: TC13 tests performance under heavy load; TC14 tests service unavailability.
Security tests: TC15 injection test covered.
gaps: Concurrency: no explicit race-condition test for concurrent DELETE operations.
Soft deletes: no explicit verification of soft vs hard delete behavior (if applicable).
Rate limiting: no tests for throttling or rate-limiting behavior.
Caching: no tests for caching headers or validation for related GET endpoints.
Authorization robustness: only missing header and token expiry tested; lack of explicit 401/403 coverage across scenarios.
Internal server error: no test simulating a 500 Internal Server Error.
Input sanitation: limited tests for unusual whitespace or case variations in headers beyond TC20.
recommendations: Add an explicit concurrency/race-condition test for DELETE while other operations modify the same invoice item.
Add tests for 401/403 responses across more authorization failure scenarios (raw tokens, revoked tokens, insufficient scopes).
Add a test that simulates a 500 Internal Server Error to verify graceful degradation.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling behavior under burst requests.
Add tests for caching behavior on related GET endpoints to ensure consistency (though DELETE typically not cached).
Add soft-delete verification if applicable, including status checks.
Enhance header validation tests with more unusual whitespace, casing, and multi-value headers to ensure robustness (in addition to TC20).
